[node name="VBoxContainer" type="VBoxContainer" parent="Panel/InstructionsPanel/ScrollContainer2"]
layout_mode = 2

[node name="Label2" type="Label" parent="Panel/InstructionsPanel/ScrollContainer2/VBoxContainer"]
layout_mode = 2
theme_override_fonts/font = ExtResource("11_dtys3")
text = "How to play
Goal: Connect your snake's head and tail (at opposite corners of the board) 
with an unbroken chain of your nodes.

The Board: A 6×6 grid where nodes are placed, 
with line intersections around the spaces where robots move.

On your turn, move exactly ONE of your robots. 
There are three move types:


A diagonal jump move a robot one space diagonally, 
and it places your node on the space it passes over, 
or flips an opponent's node to your color.


An orthogonal move shifts a robot one space up, down, left, or right 
without affecting any nodes, useful for repositioning. 

Capturing lets you jump over one opponent robot in a straight line into an empty space, 
removing that robot from the game.
You cannot capture your own robots"

